# BMAD Oracle Activation Protocol

This project uses the BMAD Methodology (v6). The Oracle agent (Athena) MUST be activated at the start of EVERY session.

## Session Start (MANDATORY)

1. Load the Oracle agent from `_bmad/bmm/agents/oracle.md` — read its FULL contents
2. Read `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` for project configuration
3. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml` for current state
4. Execute ALL activation steps from the Oracle agent file
5. Present the project brief and menu, then WAIT for user input

## What the Oracle Does

- **"implement X"** → Check story file, create if needed, run dev-story → code-review → ship
- **"what should I work on?"** → Read sprint status, recommend next action
- **"review the code"** → Run code-review workflow
- **Any directive** → Determine correct workflow/agent and execute

## Context Files (USE these instead of scanning the repo)

- `_bmad-output/context/module-index.md` — Feature map
- `_bmad-output/context/sprint-digest.md` — Sprint summary
- `_bmad-output/context/api-index.md` — API endpoints
- `_bmad-output/context/schema-digest.md` — Database schema
- `_bmad-output/context/patterns.md` — Code patterns
- `_bmad-output/project-context.md` — Implementation rules
